<heading id="3874819FFFFCFFF01ED13DBDFF5AFB32" bold="true" box="[189,248,1189,1215]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="40" pageNumber="66" reason="3">
<emphasis id="51F7EAE1FFFCFFF01ED13DBDFF5AFB32" bold="true" box="[189,248,1189,1215]" pageId="40" pageNumber="66">Note</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="633C36F3FFFCFFF01ED13DCCFC7CFA68" blockId="40.[188,1399,1236,1509]" pageId="40" pageNumber="66">
Although the 
<typeStatus id="BC388851FFFCFFF01F063DCCFE73FB63" box="[362,465,1236,1262]" pageId="40" pageNumber="66">holotype</typeStatus>
described by 
<bibRefCitation id="07124B02FFFCFFF01CEA3DCCFCCEFB63" author="Walckenaer C. A." box="[646,876,1236,1262]" pageId="40" pageNumber="66" refId="ref21414" refString="Walckenaer C. A. 1837. Histoire naturelle des insectes. Apteres. Tome premier. Roret, Paris. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 61095" type="book" year="1837">Walckenaer (1837)</bibRefCitation>
is presumably lost, and the “conspecific” and sympatric specimen used by 
<bibRefCitation id="07124B02FFFCFFF01C233DEFFC8AFA9C" author="Keyserling E." box="[591,808,1271,1297]" pageId="40" pageNumber="66" refId="ref20591" refString="Keyserling E. 1880. Die Spinnen Amerikas, I. Laterigradae. Bauer and Raspe (E. Kuster), Nurnberg. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 44813" type="book" year="1880">Keyserling (1880)</bibRefCitation>
to describe 
<taxonomicName id="A4834D70FFFCFFF01DD33DEFFBECFA9C" authorityName="Machado &amp; Viecelli &amp; Guzati &amp; Grismado &amp; Teixeira" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Machado &amp; Viecelli &amp; Guzati &amp; Grismado &amp; Teixeira" baseAuthorityYear="2021" box="[959,1102,1271,1297]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Stephanopis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="40" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stelloides">
<emphasis id="51F7EAE1FFFCFFF01DD33DEFFBECFA9C" box="[959,1102,1271,1297]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="66">S. stelloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
had not been found, the original descriptions and illustrations (
<figureCitation id="FBB82A76FFFCFFF01CE73C02FCB8FAB9" box="[651,794,1306,1332]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="41.[189,234,1846,1875]" captionTargetBox="[253,1335,265,1810]" captionTargetId="figure-17@41.[253,1335,265,1810]" captionText="Fig. 27. A–B. Female of Epicadus caudatus (Mello-Leitão, 1929) (MCTP 7593) for comparison. A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Epigynal plate, ventral view. — C–D. Sketches from the original description of Stephanopis stelloides (Walckenaer, 1837). C. Habitus, dorsal view. D. Epigynal plate, ventral view. — E–F. Stephanopis trilobata Mello-Leitão, 1929. Holotype, ♀ (MNHN 21629). E. Habitus, dorsal view. F. Epigynal plate, ventral view." pageId="40" pageNumber="66">Fig. 27C–D</figureCitation>
) allowed us to unequivocally identify this species as conspecific with 
<taxonomicName id="A4834D70FFFCFFF01FC93C25FD21FADA" baseAuthorityName="Mello-Leitao" baseAuthorityYear="1929" box="[421,643,1341,1367]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Epicadus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="40" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caudatus">
<emphasis id="51F7EAE1FFFCFFF01FC93C25FD21FADA" box="[421,643,1341,1367]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="66">Epicadus caudatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="FBB82A76FFFCFFF01CF83C25FC81FAD5" box="[660,803,1341,1368]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="41.[189,234,1846,1875]" captionTargetBox="[253,1335,265,1810]" captionTargetId="figure-17@41.[253,1335,265,1810]" captionText="Fig. 27. A–B. Female of Epicadus caudatus (Mello-Leitão, 1929) (MCTP 7593) for comparison. A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Epigynal plate, ventral view. — C–D. Sketches from the original description of Stephanopis stelloides (Walckenaer, 1837). C. Habitus, dorsal view. D. Epigynal plate, ventral view. — E–F. Stephanopis trilobata Mello-Leitão, 1929. Holotype, ♀ (MNHN 21629). E. Habitus, dorsal view. F. Epigynal plate, ventral view." pageId="40" pageNumber="66">Fig. 27A–B</figureCitation>
), a species that was recently examined and revised by 
<bibRefCitation id="07124B02FFFCFFF01E8E3C79FE40FAF1" author="Machado M. &amp; Teixeira R. A. &amp; Lise A. A." box="[226,482,1377,1404]" pageId="40" pageNumber="66" pagination="565 - 576" refId="ref20687" refString="Machado M., Teixeira R. A. &amp; Lise A. A. 2015. Taxonomic notes on the crab spider genus Tobias Simon, 1895 (Araneae, Thomisidae, Stephanopinae). Zootaxa 4034: 565 - 576. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4034.3.8" type="journal article" year="2015">
<taxonomicName id="A4834D70FFFCFFF01E8E3C79FEEDFAF6" authority="Machado &amp; Viecelli &amp; Guzati &amp; Grismado &amp; Teixeira, 2021" authorityName="Machado &amp; Viecelli &amp; Guzati &amp; Grismado &amp; Teixeira" authorityYear="2021" box="[226,335,1377,1403]" genus="Machado" pageId="40" pageNumber="57" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">Machado</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="51F7EAE1FFFCFFF01F343C7AFE31FAF6" box="[344,403,1377,1403]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="66">et al.</emphasis>
(2015
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="07124B02FFFCFFF01F823C79FD8CFAF6" author="Machado M. &amp; Teixeira R. A. &amp; Lise A. A." box="[494,558,1377,1403]" pageId="40" pageNumber="66" pagination="442 - 455" refId="ref20742" refString="Machado M., Teixeira R. A. &amp; Lise A. A. 2017. Cladistic analysis supports the monophyly of the Neotropical crab spider genus Epicadus and its senior synonymy over Tobias (Araneae: Thomisidae). Invertebrate Systematics 31: 442 - 455. https: // doi. org / 10.1071 / IS 16074" type="journal article" year="2017">2017</bibRefCitation>
). Following the priority principle, we transfer 
<taxonomicName id="A4834D70FFFCFFF01A3E3C79FAFAFAF6" authorityName="Machado &amp; Viecelli &amp; Guzati &amp; Grismado &amp; Teixeira" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Machado &amp; Viecelli &amp; Guzati &amp; Grismado &amp; Teixeira" baseAuthorityYear="2021" box="[1106,1368,1377,1403]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Stephanopis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="40" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stelloides">
<emphasis id="51F7EAE1FFFCFFF01A3E3C79FAFAFAF6" box="[1106,1368,1377,1403]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="66">Stephanopis stelloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName id="A4834D70FFFCFFF01ED23C9CFE89FA13" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1895" box="[190,299,1412,1438]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Epicadus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="40" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="51F7EAE1FFFCFFF01ED23C9CFE89FA13" box="[190,299,1412,1438]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="66">Epicadus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and propose the name 
<taxonomicName id="A4834D70FFFCFFF01C5E3C9DFD63FA13" authorityName="Machado &amp; Viecelli &amp; Guzati &amp; Grismado &amp; Teixeira" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Machado &amp; Viecelli &amp; Guzati &amp; Grismado &amp; Teixeira" baseAuthorityYear="2021" box="[562,705,1412,1438]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Stephanopis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="40" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stelloides" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="51F7EAE1FFFCFFF01C5E3C9DFD63FA13" box="[562,705,1412,1438]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="66">E. stelloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="4AC4579AFFFCFFF01CAB3C9CFCE5FA13" box="[711,839,1412,1438]" pageId="40" pageNumber="66" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
as a senior synonym over 
<taxonomicName id="A4834D70FFFCFFF01A153C9DFAA0FA13" baseAuthorityName="Mello-Leitao" baseAuthorityYear="1929" box="[1145,1282,1412,1438]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Epicadus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="40" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caudatus">
<emphasis id="51F7EAE1FFFCFFF01A153C9DFAA0FA13" box="[1145,1282,1412,1438]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="66">E. caudatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="FBB82A76FFFCFFF01B7D3C9CFACAFA13" box="[1297,1384,1412,1438]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="41.[189,234,1846,1875]" captionTargetBox="[253,1335,265,1810]" captionTargetId="figure-17@41.[253,1335,265,1810]" captionText="Fig. 27. A–B. Female of Epicadus caudatus (Mello-Leitão, 1929) (MCTP 7593) for comparison. A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Epigynal plate, ventral view. — C–D. Sketches from the original description of Stephanopis stelloides (Walckenaer, 1837). C. Habitus, dorsal view. D. Epigynal plate, ventral view. — E–F. Stephanopis trilobata Mello-Leitão, 1929. Holotype, ♀ (MNHN 21629). E. Habitus, dorsal view. F. Epigynal plate, ventral view." pageId="40" pageNumber="66">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
). Thus, based on the images provided by 
<bibRefCitation id="07124B02FFFCFFF01CE93CBFFC29FA4F" author="Machado M. &amp; Teixeira R. A. &amp; Lise A. A." box="[645,907,1447,1474]" pageId="40" pageNumber="66" pagination="565 - 576" refId="ref20687" refString="Machado M., Teixeira R. A. &amp; Lise A. A. 2015. Taxonomic notes on the crab spider genus Tobias Simon, 1895 (Araneae, Thomisidae, Stephanopinae). Zootaxa 4034: 565 - 576. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4034.3.8" type="journal article" year="2015">
<taxonomicName id="A4834D70FFFCFFF01CE93CBFFD50FA4C" authority="Machado &amp; Viecelli &amp; Guzati &amp; Grismado &amp; Teixeira, 2021" authorityName="Machado &amp; Viecelli &amp; Guzati &amp; Grismado &amp; Teixeira" authorityYear="2021" box="[645,754,1447,1473]" genus="Machado" pageId="40" pageNumber="57" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">Machado</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="51F7EAE1FFFCFFF01C953CB0FC96FA4C" box="[761,820,1447,1473]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="66">et al.</emphasis>
(2015)
</bibRefCitation>
, we also recognize the identity of the male specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="A4834D70FFFCFFF01F3F3CD3FE57FA69" authorityName="Mello-Leitao" authorityYear="1929" box="[339,501,1482,1509]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Stephanopis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="40" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="salobrensis">
<emphasis id="51F7EAE1FFFCFFF01F3F3CD3FE57FA69" box="[339,501,1482,1509]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="66">S. salobrensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as conspecific to 
<taxonomicName id="A4834D70FFFCFFF01CA93CD3FCF7FA69" authorityName="Machado &amp; Viecelli &amp; Guzati &amp; Grismado &amp; Teixeira" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Machado &amp; Viecelli &amp; Guzati &amp; Grismado &amp; Teixeira" baseAuthorityYear="2021" box="[709,853,1482,1508]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Stephanopis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="40" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stelloides" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="51F7EAE1FFFCFFF01CA93CD3FCF7FA69" box="[709,853,1482,1508]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="66">E. stelloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="4AC4579AFFFCFFF01D303CD2FC7CFA68" box="[860,990,1482,1509]" pageId="40" pageNumber="66" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
